parameters.toolDescription: Use this tool to fetch all available documents, including the table schema if the file is a CSV or Excel file.
Given a file ID, fetches the text from the document.
parameters.query:
SELECT 
    string_agg(content, ' ') as document_text
FROM documents
  WHERE metadata->>'file_id' = $1
GROUP BY metadata->>'file_id';

parameters.toolDescription: Use RAG to look up information in the knowledgebase.

-- T·∫°o b·∫£ng l∆∞u metadata c·ªßa t√†i li·ªáu
CREATE TABLE document_metadata (

-- T·∫°o b·∫£ng l∆∞u c√°c d√≤ng d·ªØ li·ªáu c·ªßa t√†i li·ªáu
CREATE TABLE document_rows (

);

-- T·∫°o b·∫£ng l∆∞u tr·ªØ t√†i li·ªáu v√† embedding c·ªßa ch√∫ng
CREATE TABLE documents (

  content TEXT,  -- N·ªôi dung t√†i li·ªáu

);

-- T·∫°o h√†m ƒë·ªÉ t√¨m ki·∫øm t√†i li·ªáu d·ª±a tr√™n embedding
CREATE FUNCTION match_documents (
  query_embedding VECTOR(1536),

  filter JSONB DEFAULT '{}'
) RETURNS TABLE (
  doc_id BIGINT,
  content TEXT,
  metadata JSONB,
  similarity FLOAT

LANGUAGE plpgsql
AS $$
BEGIN
  RETURN QUERY
  SELECT
    documents.id AS doc_id,  -- ƒê·ªïi t√™n c·ªôt 'id' c·ªßa b·∫£ng 'documents' th√†nh 'doc_id'
    documents.content,

  JOIN document_metadata ON documents.id = document_metadata.id  -- Li√™n k·∫øt v·ªõi b·∫£ng document_metadata
  LEFT JOIN document_rows ON document_metadata.id = document_rows.dataset_id  -- Li√™n k·∫øt v·ªõi b·∫£ng document_rows
  WHERE documents.metadata @> filter

END;
$$;
